# Kinematic Formulas for Uniform Acceleration

 1. Acceleration Formula

 v = v0 + at

 v = final velocity (m/s)
 v0 = initial velocity (m/s)
 a = acceleration (m/s^2)
 t = time (s)

 Since the object starts from rest, v0 = 0:
 v = at

 2. Displacement Formula

 x = x0 + v0*t + 0.5 * a * t^2

 x = final position (displacement, meters)
 x0 = initial position (meters)
 v0 = initial velocity (m/s)
 a = acceleration (m/s^2)
 t = time (s)

 Since the object starts from rest, v0 = 0:
 x = 0.5 * a * t^2

 3. Alternative Formula for Velocity (without time)

 v^2 = v0^2 + 2a * (x - x0)
 
 v = final velocity (m/s)
 v0 = initial velocity (m/s)
 a = acceleration (m/s^2)
 x = final displacement (meters)
 x0 = initial displacement (meters)